{"word":"ἀστήρ","slug":"ἀστήρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀστήρ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>The Root is <el>ΣΤΕΡ</el>, <el>α</el> being <i><a href='S:euphonic'>euphon.</a></i> , <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>stella</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>sterula</i>.\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> = <el>ἄστρασι</el> not <el>ἀστράσι</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a star</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ἄστρον.</el><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a flame, light, fire</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}